The Vaccinometer was developed by Dr. Larry Glickman of Purdue University (Table 5-3
). It is intended for use by veterinarians to help them determine necessity of vaccination in a given situation. The company Merial has developed a tool that uses lifestyle considerations to determine which vaccines should be given (Table 5-4
). Breeders and pet owners are strongly encouraged to discuss vaccination frequency with their veterinarian.
